Below is a ready-to-use JSON payload you can pass to curl to launch an AWX/Ansible Controller Job Template (or Workflow Template) for your JVM restart automation.

I’m assuming:

Your playbook expects the payload variable name jvm_restart
And the structure is env → hosts → profiles → jvms.
1) JSON payload (extra_vars) for the Job Template launch
Example (DEV + PROD in same request)
{
  "extra_vars": {
    "jvm_restart": {
      "ritm_number": "RITM1234",
      "envs": {
        "dev": {
          "hosts": {
            "test1": {
              "AppSrv01": ["server1", "server2"]
            },
            "test2": {
              "AppSrv02": ["server3", "server4"]
            }
          }
        },
        "prod": {
          "hosts": {
            "prodapp1": {
              "AppSrvP01": ["server1"]
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
2) curl for AWX/Controller Job Template launch
Basic Auth
curl -k -X POST \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -u "awx_user:awx_password" \
  "https://AWX_HOST/api/v2/job_templates/JOB_TEMPLATE_ID/launch/" \
  -d '{
    "extra_vars": {
      "jvm_restart": {
        "ritm_number": "RITM1234",
        "envs": {
          "dev": {
            "hosts": {
              "test1": { "AppSrv01": ["server1", "server2"] },
              "test2": { "AppSrv02": ["server3", "server4"] }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }'
Bearer Token
curl -k -X POST \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE" \
  "https://AWX_HOST/api/v2/job_templates/JOB_TEMPLATE_ID/launch/" \
  -d '{
    "extra_vars": {
      "jvm_restart": {
        "ritm_number": "RITM1234",
        "envs": {
          "dev": {
            "hosts": {
              "test1": { "AppSrv01": ["server1", "server2"] }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }'
3) If you need to set inventory / limit / verbosity in the same launch

(Some Controller setups allow these fields; if not, Controller will reject them.)

{
  "inventory": 12,
  "limit": "test1,test2",
  "verbosity": 2,
  "extra_vars": {
    "jvm_restart": {
      "ritm_number": "RITM1234",
      "envs": {
        "dev": {
          "hosts": {
            "test1": { "AppSrv01": ["server1", "server2"] },
            "test2": { "AppSrv02": ["server3"] }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
Notes (so it works smoothly)
Host keys like "test1" must match reachable inventory hostnames in Controller (or resolvable DNS).
If your job template doesn’t allow inventory override or limit override, remove those fields.
The payload should be passed exactly under "extra_vars": { "jvm_restart": ... }.

If you tell me whether you’re launching a Job Template or Workflow Template, and what fields your template allows on launch (inventory/limit/credentials), I can tailor the exact curl body to match Controller validation rules.
